  "texts": [
    "As explained in Section 2, we use uid provided in the LAMOST catalogs to distinguish between stellar sources observed by MRS. Each record in the LAMOST MRS Parameter Catalog corresponds to a MRS observation (and a coadded spectrum) and has a unique obsid.",
    "A stellar source (uid) with three or more MRS observations (obsid) after all the screening conditions described in Section 3.1 is considered as a timedomain object employed in this work.",
    "For clarity, we use N obs to represent the number of MRS observations of a stellar source, then the criterion for a time-domain object can be expressed as N obs ≥ 3.",
    "Only the stellar sources that meet this criterion are kept in our sample.",
    "Another key parameter for a time-domain object is the time span of multiple observations (denoted by T span), which is defined as the time difference between the first and last MRS observations for the object."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}